{"title": "Chief Legatee", "description": "\"I was married to-day in Grace Church. At the altar my bride--you probably know her name, Miss Georgian Hazen--wore a natural look, and was in all respects, so far as any one could see, a happy woman, satisfied with her choice and pleased with the \u00e9clat and elegancies of the occasion. Half-way down the aisle this all changed. I remember the instant perfectly. Her hand was on my arm and I felt it suddenly stiffen. I was not alarmed, but I gave her a quick look and saw that something had happened....<br>\n...I should have passed the matter over as a mere attack of nerves, if I had not afterwards detected in her face, through all the hurry and excitement of the ensuing reception, a strained expression not at all natural to her. This was still more evident after the congratulations of a certain guest, who, I am sure, whispered to her before he passed on...<br>\n...She entered the office with me and was standing close at my side all the time I was writing our names in the register; but later, when I turned to ask her to enter the elevator with me, she was gone...\" (Excerpts from Chapter 1)", "duration": 25260, "language": "English", "authors": [{"id": "407", "name": "Anna Katharine Green"}], "coverArt": "https://archive.org/download/LibrivoxCdCoverArt33/chief_legatee_1412.jpg", "copyright_year": "1906", "genres": ["Detective Fiction"], "supporters": [{"role": "Read by", "name": "Tony Oliva"}, {"role": "Book Coordinator", "name": "Tony Oliva"}, {"role": "Meta Coordinator", "name": "J. M. Smallheer"}, {"role": "Proof Listener", "name": "DaveC"}], "sections": [{"section": 1, "title": "A Bride of Five Hours", "readers": [6671], "path": "https://www.archive.org/download/chief_legatee_1412_librivox/chieflegatee_01_green_64kb.mp3", "duration": 1150}, {"section": 2, "title": "The Lady in Number Three", "readers": [6671], "path": "https://www.archive.org/download/chief_legatee_1412_librivox/chieflegatee_02_green_64kb.mp3", "durati